	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
				<date>11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May &#39;56</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">It was only upon looking into the<lb/>
				<date>May</date> Occident received two days since&#44; that I <sic>learnd</sic> of
				your serious<lb/> loss by fire. <persName>Miss Gratz&#39;s</persName> letter
				informing <persName>Mrs <del>&#63;</del> Joseph</persName> of the<lb/> occident only
				reached here a day before and I had not seen <persName>Mrs J.</persName><lb/> for
				some days. While I sincerely regret your loss has been so great<lb/> I cannot but
				think you fortunate in having preserved your plate<lb/> which will render the
				reproduction of your books a matter of<lb/> no great labor or loss of time. I beg
				leave to subjoin a list of the<lb/> books with which I have been favored either by
				you or <persName>Mr M Joseph</persName><lb/> for sale</p>
			<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline">Statement</hi></p>
			<table rows="22" cols="3">
				<row>
					<cell role="label">Books received</cell>
					<cell role="label">To Whom Sold</cell>
					<cell role="label">Remarks</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>per <persName>Mr Joseph</persName></cell>
					<cell/>
					<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>2 sets Prayers</cell>
					<cell>1 <persName>W. Benjamin</persName></cell>
					<cell>paid <date>8 Feb. 55</date> and</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 <persName>B W Warner</persName></cell>
					<cell>amount have <add>&#63;</add> to Mr</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell/>
					<cell><persName>Joseph</persName> as per his receipt.</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>2 sets Pentateuch</cell>
					<cell>unsold</cell>
					<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>6 2&#44;to English Bibles</cell>
					<cell>unsold</cell>
					<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>11 <persName>Dias&#39;</persName> Letters</cell>
					<cell>3 sold<persName> Asher Benjamin</persName></cell>
					<cell>Pd <date>8 Feb</date> as per <persName>Mr Joseph</persName></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>25 <persName>Pichatto</persName></cell>
					<cell>unsold</cell>
					<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>1 <date>Kipoor</date> Book</cell>
					<cell><persName>Mr Benjamin</persName></cell>
					<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>recd per <persName>Mr Leeser</persName></cell>
					<cell/>
					<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>4 sets Prayers</cell>
					<cell>1 <persName>M Kortosk</persName></cell>
					<cell>Pd <date>18 Feb 55</date> as per <persName>Mr Joseph</persName></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 <persName>L Benjamin</persName></cell>
					<cell><date>15 Aug 55</date>
						<add>&#63;</add></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 Kablinstic<add>&#63;</add></cell>
					<cell><date>12 Decr 55</date>
						<add>&#63;</add></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 <persName>S Hyman</persName></cell>
					<cell>not yet paid</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell>6 Daily <add>&#63;</add></cell>
					<cell>1 <persName>L Benjamin</persName></cell>
					<cell>Pd <date>15 Aug&#39;55</date>
						<add>&#63;</add></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 <persName>L Moss</persName></cell>
					<cell>Pd <date>12 Dec 55</date>
						<add>&#63;</add></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 <persName>E Moss</persName></cell>
					<cell><hi rend="underline">these two Daily prayers</hi> Pd <date>14 Feb
							&#39;56</date></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 <persName>G Benjamin</persName></cell>
					<cell><hi rend="underline">were not paid <persName>Mr J.</persName></hi> Pd
							<date>13 March &#39;56</date></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1</cell>
					<cell>as I waited to</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell>1 not paid</cell>
					<cell>remit you a large</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell/>
					<cell/>
					<cell>amount</cell>
				</row>
			</table>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p>The payments have been so tardy that I find myself unwarranted<lb/> to send you an
				order for books. I feel my inclination to do so<lb/> much greater than my
				ability&#44; still if you like to send a couple<lb/> of sets &#38; a few Dailys I
				will try what I can do with them<lb/> I will remit you per <persName>Mr
					Joseph</persName> for the set sold <persName>Mr S Hymans</persName>
					&#40;<add>&#63;</add><lb/> west to the Dame <add>&#63;</add>&#8212;perhaps a
				line from you may be effective&#41;<lb/> though I <sic>dont</sic> think he will pay
				for it just yet&#8212;he has frequently<lb/> been asked. I want no disconnect on it
				thinking it scarcely<lb/> fair for you to pay it on such long credits. I will also
				remit<lb/> you for<lb/>
				<date>Kipoor</date> &#38; 2 Daily. The copies of the <persName>Soto</persName> Bible
				sent<lb/> out I know nothing about. <persName>Mr J.</persName> sent them out and I
				believe<lb/> had tried to collect the amounts&#44; but as I have not deemed<lb/>
				myself authorized to interfere I have refrained from pressing<lb/> payment&#44; but
				if you send me a line &#40;which I can show&#41; requesting<lb/> me to obtain
				payment for you I think I may be able to do<lb/> something for you. With respect to
				the Occident it is not my<lb/> fault if it has not more readers here&#44; for
				although I may<lb/> have deemed its conduct towards me not over generous&#44; I
				have<lb/> always recommended it as the superb<add>&#63;</add> Jewish magazine&#44;
				but<lb/> my people are very like their brethren <add>&#63;</add> side the lines<lb/>
				<hi rend="underline">the Journal</hi>&#44; ledger &#38; cash Book have great
				interest as serious<lb/> reading while for lighter moments the Book of Kings
				&#40;&#38; <add>&#63;</add>&#41;<lb/> obtain their share of attention. Do you intend
				to <add>&#63;</add> your<lb/> weekly&#63;</p> 
			<p rend="indent(4)">I am dear sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
